The article is a message from former President Barack Obama to Congress, regarding the continuation of the national emergency with respect to the situation in or in relation to the Democratic Republic of the Congo. This national emergency was declared in Executive Order 13413 in 2006 and is set to expire on October 27, 2013. Obama states that the situation in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, characterized by widespread violence and atrocities, poses a threat to regional stability and the foreign policy of the United States. As a result, he deems it necessary to extend the national emergency.